reviewText: The subject of this documentary was eye catching, but unfortunately the production was a mixed bag and unfortunately did not have much objectivity or feminist criticism.  A few cautionary tales, but nothing that you couldn't do without.  I suspect "Doctor" Fisher's credentials were obtained from a mail order catalog.

reviewText: This is a documentary about the role of breasts in American culture and is focused on women who decide to have implants or breast reduction (or removal for health reasons). For me, it was perhaps rather superficial in terms of both female and male psychology. There are interviews with women who decide to have this plastic surgery and their male partners also give opinions. We also see the surgery in progress and the end results. The term 'Hollywood Perfect' is used to describe the ultimate breast and that is perhaps a clue to the American Dream theme that powers this huge industry in the US. I would rate the documentary as three stars and perhaps worth a viewing. Ideal drink for viewing pleasure: of course milk.

reviewText: My niece, a tween girl, and I stumbled across this looking for something to watch on streaming video. We watched it together. We both thought it was interesting and thought-provoking. I can't say that I learned anything new, but the film is well done and my friend learned a lot about the role of boobs in our culture. Some things she has experienced, witnessed, overheard, seen in movies, etc., but didn't really understand, were explained in the film. We have had several interesting conversations since we viewed it. I think it is a useful film especially for teenage girls.

reviewText: Interesting film about Boobs. Includes brest enlargement, reduction, and masectomies. Great commentaries are provided, one of the best being by Mamie Van Doren. Being an entertainer who has usually been categorized by her bust size, she is definitely qualified to give her opinion. I have met Mamie and she is so nice to her fans. I admire her stand on women'sand gay rights. A living legend and one of the last stars of the Golden Age of Hollywood.
